{
  "texts": [
    "10, 𝛼 is the key hyper-parameter that controls the contribution of the contrastive loss L 𝑐𝑙.",
    "Hence, in this subsection, we explore the impacts of 𝛼 on FELLAS.Figure 6 shows the performance trends of FELLAS with increasing values of 𝛼 from 0.001 to 1.0 across three datasets.",
    "Generally, as 𝛼 increases, the model performance also improves until it reaches a peak, confirming the effectiveness of our contrastive enhancement.",
    "However, beyond this peak, further increasing the value of 𝛼 causes a decline in model performance, as the contrastive task becomes too dominant and significantly hinders the learning of the recommendation task.",
    "For instance, on the Beauty dataset, FELLAS achieves its best performance when 𝛼 = 0.001, meanwhile, for the Office and PLG datasets, increasing 𝛼 to 0.1 positively influences the recommendation model."
  ]
}